This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with evaluating saliency models' ability to predict where humans look in images. Additionally, the paper discusses different evaluation metrics and their properties, which are commonly used in computer vision research. The paper also touches upon artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it discusses the use of saliency models in these fields. The paper also has relevance to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it deals with how humans interact with images and how saliency models can be used to predict this interaction. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with image analysis and evaluation.
